::'''Wen Shiqi:''' Let me double-check everything: Research topic, no progress; research progress report meeting, canceled last minute; performance review criteria, under evaluation...
::'''Wen Shiqi:''' Good! Everything's in place! Now, this is the best time for scientific research.
::'''Wen Shiqi:''' Uh-huh... I don't think I've seen you before. Nevertheless, it seems to be our fate to meet each other like this, especially during the leisure time away from work.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_500010118_994-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_500010118_994-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You don't look very busy.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_500011506-->
:::'''Wen Shiqi:''' That's not true. How busy I am should not be judged by any existing projects, but whether any brainstorming is happening in my head. This is my work philosophy.
:::'''Wen Shiqi:''' Although I may seem pretty leisurely, deep down I do care a lot about the space station's restoration after the Legion invasion!
:::'''Wen Shiqi:''' Have you noticed how intertwined my eyebrows are right now? That's how much I care about the space station.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Don't you have work to do?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_500011510-->
:::'''Wen Shiqi:''' What should be counted as work? Is it sitting behind a desk all day, devoting all your life to some random pieces of ill-defined data? Or racking your brain, trying to come up with a way to deliver convincing arguments for the sake of a performance review?
:::'''Wen Shiqi:''' Outward appearance doesn't say anything about your work attitude. If your mind is not in work mode, how is it any different from slacking off at work?
:::'''Wen Shiqi:''' Similarly, thinking about work during your break is what should be considered as true devotion to your work. You got it?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_500010118_1004-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_500010118_1004-->
